main event: Two round objects, the size of a dime, were observed changing colors at dawn in W Los Angeles, California.
interesting points: The objects resembled a star and appeared to blot out by the rising sun., The objects were thought to be aircraft but the duration of observation was excessive for an aircraft., The sighting lasted for about 35 minutes., There was some confusion regarding the disappearance of the objects, as they either went over the hills or were obscured by light., Insufficient data is given for a conclusive evaluation of the sighting.
